<br>
I talked to my chanter friend about this and he said he wouldn't want to be a chanter/cleric with only one bank of spell gems simply because he doen't have enough to keep all the spells memmed he wants NOW.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, don't forget that you could easily end up with poor stats if you play something thats not compatible with your stats.  Such as a DE rogue that DC's into a Necro is probably not going to have very good Int.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As for hp and mana, they should not be cumulative.  ie. when you level up to level 10 in a class, you wouldn't have the hp/mana of that class at that level added to your pools, but rather, the higher of the 2 would apply.<br>
<br>
As a hypothetical example, if your a shaman, and at level 10 your shaman got another 50 hp and 50 mana.  And now, your a warrior and the warrior would get 100hp and no mana at level 10.  So taking the higher of each, you'd have 100hp and 50mana.  But since you alread have 50 and 50 of that, when you hit level 10 in warrior, it would simply add 50hps to your max hps.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As for when you should be able to dual class, I think the best way to handle it is that once you hit level 60 you simply go to the applicable guild master in your home town and get your first level in your new class awarded to you.  As for AA points, I don't think any AA points should be required to dual class, and I think that AA points should still be gainable at any time while you are dual classing, since it's a seperate exp bar that you can set yourself.  And as you meet the AA requirements for your next class, those powers would be added to the AA list of powers you could purchase. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unakilosgaremonde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakilos Garemonde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 12:57:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23061.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idea for new charactor advancement...</span><hr size=1> I just want them to add quests which result in AA skills. Something reasonably difficult and extensive, but the skill would be great. Excellent RP value, and a really good skill > more stats from items. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31317">Master Nakilos the Illusionist (60 Phantasmist)</a>   <a href="Http://www.keepersofthefaith.org">  &lt;Keepers of the Faith&gt; </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uavissuprema.showPublicProfile?language=EN>avissuprema</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>R